I discovered RSS a few days back and have been searching around for good blogs to fill my feed. 
I found a few great blogs here on HN:<p>[1] https:&#x2F;&#x2F;alien.slackbook.org&#x2F;blog&#x2F;
[2] https:&#x2F;&#x2F;acoup.blog&#x2F;
[3] https:&#x2F;&#x2F;scholars-stage.org&#x2F;<p>Are there any other active blogs that fill this template of long and deep discussions on a particular topic by an individual?<p>I&#x27;m particularly interested in books, philosophy and electronics blogs though any topic will do as long as it&#x27;s not deep level programming.<p>It doesn&#x27;t necessarily need to have an RSS feed because I&#x27;ll try some workarounds if it is interesting enough.<p>Though not particularly related, old-style one-man informative sites (and not blogs) are also welcome.
